  "slug": "rabbit-pie",
  "title": "Rabbit Pie",
  "subtitle": "Slow-braised wild rabbit in a mustard and cream sauce, under a puff pastry lid",
  "excerpt": "Rabbit is the most underused British meat: cheap, lean, and flavourful. Jointed and braised in white wine with mustard and cream, then set under a puff pastry lid, it makes a deeply satisfying pie that takes less effort than it suggests.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British game cookery. Jane Grigson, English Food (1974): rabbit in mustard sauce. Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136: rabbit pie method. Traditional British farmhouse cooking.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rabbit is a lean meat that benefits from the same approach as pheasant: a little fat added during cooking and a method that adds moisture. Ask the butcher to ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "joint",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4l6b0000sov4achf9b9l"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " the rabbit for you when you buy it. Here the fat comes from lardons fried at the start, and the moisture from a white wine and cream sauce. The result, after the rabbit has braised for 90 minutes, is meat that pulls from the bones with no resistance.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "After braising, pick all the meat from the bones before filling the pie. The small bones of a rabbit leg are easy to find when you are looking for them, but embarrassing in a pie when you are not. A ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "mustard cream sauce",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4l760001sov4wmgagzwe"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " finishes the braising liquid; the mustard goes in off the heat, not into the hot pan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
